[1] Bacterial leaf blight - Kerala
Date: Mon 10 Sep 2018 06:05 AM IST
Source: New Indian Express [edited]
http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2018/sep/10/crop-disease-deals-a-double-blow-to-kerala-peasants-1869846.html


[In] Kerala, post the devastating floods, leaf blight disease inflicted severe damage on paddy crops. Crops grown using an overdose of nitrogen fertilisers had been affected the most as the bacterial disease will be more virulent. The Agriculture Department found it [in] crops which reached the booting and flowering stage.

"Even in the crops which survived the vegetative phase, the yield could be very low," said M C Narayanankutty, Regional Agriculture Research Station. The standing crop has been damaged along with seed nurseries and beds. The rice from the affected areas will be broken and the hay will also be in truncated form.

[Byline: A Satish]

